summary:
Welcoming the Secretary-General's report (S/2011/549);

Determining the situation in Somalia remains a threat to international peace and security;

Acting under Chapter VII:

1. Authorizes the African Union to maintain AMISOM deployment until 31 October 2012, with a mandate to take necessary measures, and requests an increase to 12,000 uniformed personnel;

2. Calls on Transitional Federal Institutions to abide by the roadmap, with clear timelines and benchmarks, and link future Council support to completion of these tasks;

3. Notes African Union Peace and Security Council recommendations and will consider progress in future decisions on AMISOM;

4. Welcomes increased UN presence in Somalia, urges a more permanent presence, particularly in Mogadishu;

5. Agrees on the need for a guard force within AMISOM to provide security for international personnel;

6. Requests the Secretary-General to provide technical advice to the African Union on AMISOM planning and deployment;

7. Welcomes AMISOM's efforts to reduce civilian casualties, urges continued efforts to protect civilians;

8. Requests AMISOM to assist in developing the Somali Police Force and National Security Force.
